# SupplyMindAI: Restart After Edits

When making changes to the SupplyMindAI app (e.g. `app.py` or any file in `SupplyMindAI/`), always:

1. **Kill** any process using port 8000:
   ```powershell
   Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.OwningProcess -gt 4 } | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }
   ```

2. **Rerun** the app:
   ```powershell
   py -m shiny run SupplyMindAI/app.py --launch-browser
   ```

Run the kill command first, then start the app. Do this automatically after each edit session.
